parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure (Water Ingress into Motherboard and Fuse Box)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water ingress into the motherboard and fuse box can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents. Additionally, it can also cause electrical system failures, which can lead to fires.
symptoms: Water entering the motherboard and fuse box
vehicle stalling
check engine warning light illumination
failure to restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in recall repair can lead to continued exposure to electrical system failures, which can cause accidents or fires.
symptoms: Notification of recall
but parts not available
manufacturer exceeding reasonable time for recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the passenger seat occupancy detector can lead to the deactivation of airbags, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Passenger airbag light constantly on
airbags not activating.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unreliable Indicator Lights and Sensor Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unreliable indicator lights and sensor issues can lead to confusion and distraction while driving, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Indicator lights coming on frequently
mechanics unable to diagnose causes
multiple repairs and replacements needed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of power steering can cause the vehicle to lose directional control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
the steering wheel feels stiff or heavy
the vehicle wanders or pulls to one side
the vehicle does not respond to steering input
the power steering warning light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and overheating can cause the vehicle to lose power and come to a sudden stop, potentially leading to accidents, especially if it occurs while driving on a highway or in heavy traffic. Additionally, engine overheating can cause damage to the engine and other components, leading to costly repairs.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts down while in motion
overheating lights and smoke appear on the dashboard
the vehicle is unable to restart
the engine stalls at a red light or while stopping.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The dealership's failure to acknowledge a valid recall can lead to delayed or inadequate repairs, putting the driver and passengers at risk of accidents or injuries due to the underlying issue.
symptoms: The dealership denies the existence of a recall despite the vehicle's make
model
and year matching the recall criteria
the dealership fails to provide accurate information about the recall status.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Faulty ignition coils can cause the engine to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: Complete loss of engine power
engine stalling
difficulty starting the engine
engine misfires
rough engine idle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbag deployment in a severe crash can lead to serious injury or even fatalities, as the occupants may not receive the necessary protection to mitigate the impact.
symptoms: Airbags fail to deploy in a crash
despite the severity of the impact
seat reclines or moves excessively during the crash
headrest breaks or detaches from its base.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat and headrest can lead to serious injury or even fatalities, as the occupants may not receive the necessary support and protection during a crash.
symptoms: Seat reclines or moves excessively during the crash
headrest breaks or detaches from its base
seat back fails to maintain its position
headrest does not provide adequate support.
